cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.DS

The paper introduces a logic for reasoning about quantitative languages of infinite words, which is a topic related to formal languages and automata theory. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of this logic for describing quantitative properties of systems, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the equivalence between the logic and weighted Buchi automata, which is a topic related to programming languages (cs.PL) and data structures (cs.DS).
